Package: xtop
Version: 0.39.1-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: journalctl, docker-compose, postgresql-client
Installed-Size: 23240
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 xtop is a terminal-based system monitor with ranked root-cause hypotheses,
 evidence scoring, and eBPF deep diagnostics. v0.39.1 adds the SRE Resource
 Share panel to the Apps (Y) page: per-dimension rank + capacity share +
 per-app contribution to the active bottleneck, with a top-5-per-dimension
 quick-view. Also includes the full v0.39.0 feature set (multi-host fleet
 hub + embedded web dashboard, incident diff vs prior similar, config-drift
 and app-log auto-correlation, runbook library, post-mortem tooling,
 VM right-sizing, named utilization baselines).
